The paper proposes a deep probabilistic model for disease progression that uses attention mechanisms and phased LSTM units to generate interpretable representations of individual-level health trajectories. This work involves machine learning, artificial intelligence, and computational modeling of complex systems, which are all relevant to the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science). Additionally, the use of LSTM units and attention mechanisms suggests a focus on neural networks and natural language processing, which are relevant to the sub-categories of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
